                    <div _ngcontent-serverapp-c35="" class="container"><div _ngcontent-serverapp-c35="" class="faq-row row"><div _ngcontent-serverapp-c35="" class="col-sm-12"><h3>Layla Memory Foam Mattress</h3><div class="row post-faq-row"><div class="col-sm-6" id="about-mattress-mattress"><h5>About The Mattress</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_592"><div class="toggtitle">1. What is the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress is a dual sided copper infused memory foam mattress. You can flip your Layla from one side to the other for two different firmness levels in one mattress.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_590"><div class="toggtitle">2. How firm is the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The soft side of the Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress would be considered a 4 out of 10 in terms of firmness. The firm side is a 7 out of 10. You can flip your Layla from one side to the other based on your comfort preferences.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_588"><div class="toggtitle">3. What are the dimensions of the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Here are the individual dimensions of each size Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress:<br> Twin 38” x 74” x 10”<br> Twin XL 38” x 80” x 10”<br> Full 54” x 74” x 10”<br> Queen 60” x 80” x 10”<br> King 76” x 80” x 10”<br> Cal King 72” x 84” x 10”</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_551"><div class="toggtitle">4. What types of foam are used in the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Layla<sup>®</sup> contains three types of foam and all foams used in the mattress are CertiPUR-US certified. The outer layers of the mattress (nearest your body) are high density copper infused memory foam, the base layer is poly foam, and the air flow layer is convoluted foam.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_555"><div class="toggtitle">5. What is the density of the foams used in the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> mattress uses a core foam with a density of 1.5 pounds. The convoluted air flow layer which supports the soft side has a density of 1.8 pounds giving you a softer feel. The Copper Infused Memory Foam (on both sides) has a density of 3.5 pounds.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_557"><div class="toggtitle">6. Are the foams in the Layla® Mattress safe?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>All foams used in the Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress are CertiPUR-US® certified, meaning the foam is:<br> Made without ozone depleters<br> Made without PBDEs, TDCPP or TCEP (”Tris”) flame retardants<br> Made without mercury, lead, and other heavy metals<br> Made without formaldehyde<br> Made without phthalates regulated by the Consumer Product Safety Commission<br> Low VOC (Volatile Organic Compound) emissions for indoor air quality (less than 0.5 parts per million) so there’s little to no off gassing odor.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1138"><div class="toggtitle">7. What is the Layla® Mattress cover made from?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress zipper cover are 66% polyester, 30% viscose, 4% poly/lycra, and is woven with a ThermoGEL cooling agent to help reduce heat buildup.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1141"><div class="toggtitle">8. How is the Layla® Mattress cooler than other mattresses?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress keeps you cooler in two ways; Copper in the foam and ThermoGEL in the cover. Copper cells in the mattress act as a super-conductor to absorb body heat and rapidly transfer it away from your body. ThermoGEL is a food grade cooling agent in the cover that activates when your body temp begins to rise to cool you down quickly.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1147"><div class="toggtitle">9. Is the Layla® Mattress fire resistant?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes. The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress uses a Ventex fire blocking sleeve which is made with 48% FR Rayon Allesandra and 52% FR Rayon Polyester. There are absolutely no chemicals added, the fire blocking elements are within the fabric itself.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1149"><div class="toggtitle">10. Is the Layla® Mattress made in the USA?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress is proudly made in the USA. Our foam is poured and the mattress assembled in the Rust belt region of the Midwestern United States. Our mattress cover and label are both made in the Southeast region of the United States. From time to time we experience heavier than normal order volume, and to avoid any backorder delays we send our American made fabric to El Salvador and Mexico to be cut and sewn.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1151"><div class="toggtitle">11. Does copper in the Layla® Mattress really make a difference?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes. There are several great benefits to sleeping on copper infused foam. Copper facilitates rapid heat transfer keeping you cooler, it provides variable support to relieve pressure points, and it provides antimicrobial protection for the mattress. <a href="https://laylasleep.com/why-copper/"> Learn more about the benefits of copper</a></p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1161"><div class="toggtitle">12. Is the Layla® Mattress good for side sleepers?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes. The soft side of the Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress was specifically designed for side sleepers. You get just the right amount of sink coupled with excellent pressure point support to keep you feeling great around your shoulder, hip, and lower back.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1163"><div class="toggtitle">13. Is financing available for the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes. We offer financing with rates from 0-30% through Affirm financing. To apply for financing simply select Affirm Financing at checkout and complete a 2 minute application. Upon approval you will be presented options for your financing term. Affirm performs a soft credit check in qualifying your application.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1165"><div class="toggtitle">14. Will the Layla® Mattress work on an adjustable base?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes. The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress conforms perfectly to an adjustable base.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1167"><div class="toggtitle">15. Is the Layla® Mattress good for motion transfer?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress has been rated one of the best mattresses online for motion transfer. If you're on YouTube, you can see a bunch of tests. That should give you a good idea if the mattress is right for you in terms of bounce and motion transfer.<br> Here's a link to some YouTube videos:<br> <a href="https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=layla+mattress+motion+transfer">https://www.youtube.com/results?search_query=layla+mattress+motion+transfer</a></p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1169"><div class="toggtitle">16. Why should I choose the Layla® Mattress over all the other brands?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>We feel the Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress stands out from the others for these reasons:<br> Copper-infused memory foam keeps you cooler.<br> ThermoGEL in the cover keeps you cooler<br> Dual sided for two firmness levels in one mattress.<br> 120 night risk free trial period.<br> 0% Easy Financing with no fee<br> Free Shipping and Free Returns in the lower 48 states<br> Industry leading Lifetime Warranty<br> 100% Made in America</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="care-mattress"><h5>Care</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1233"><div class="toggtitle">1. How do I flip the Layla® Mattress from the soft side to the firm side?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Flipping from soft to firm on a Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress is easy. Remove your bedding and flip the mattress over. Done. See how easy that is?</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1230"><div class="toggtitle">2. How often should I rotate the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>We suggest rotating your mattress from head to foot each time you change your bedding, or at least one time per month.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1227"><div class="toggtitle">3. Can I place a cover or protector on the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes, you may place a cover or protector on the Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress if you so desire however, keep in mind that any additional covering on the mattress may diminish the cooling properties of the mattress to some extent. To minimize reduction of cooling effects, we suggest a cover or protector made from a highly breathable material.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1224"><div class="toggtitle">4. Can I place the mattress directly on the floor?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>You can put a Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress directly on the floor, but we don't recommend it long-term as it's not best for airflow and moisture accumulation and may void your warranty.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_559"><div class="toggtitle">5. How long after unboxing before I can sleep on the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress will take its’ full shape within minutes and you can sleep on it right away. For those who are sensitive to smell, you may detect a slight “new mattress” smell after unboxing. This odor is not harmful to your health, but if it bothers you we recommend allowing a few hours in a well ventilated room before placing any bedding on the mattress.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_561"><div class="toggtitle">6. Can I wash the mattress cover?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>We recommend dry cleaning to maintain the plush and soft feel of the mattress cover. You may purchase additional or replacement covers by contacting us at <a href="mailto:support@laylasleep.com">support@laylasleep.com</a>.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_586"><div class="toggtitle">7. What type of foundation should I use for the Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>You can put your Layla<sup>®</sup> on a box spring (if your bed frame requires one), or a platform bed as long as the slats are 3 inches apart or less. Those are the best options for support and maximum airflow for the mattress.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="return-exchange-mattress"><h5>Trial Period / Warranty &amp; Returns</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1269"><div class="toggtitle">1. How do I return my Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>If you have slept on your Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress for at least two weeks and decided that it’s not the right fit for you, you may initiate a return by emailing us your order number and the reason for your return to <a href="mailto:support@laylasleep.com">support@laylasleep.com</a>.</p><p>Your Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress will be picked up from you as is, so there's no need to save the box or repackage the mattress. We partner with local non-profits and charitable organizations to re-purpose your returned mattress, so you know it's not going to waste.</p><p>Returns are free and we don't deduct a single penny, you can purchase your Layla knowing that there's absolutely no risk. And if you return it, a local charity will reap the benefits... everyone wins!<br> *Shipping fees to AK, HI, and Canada are non-refundable.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1265"><div class="toggtitle">2. What does the Layla® Mattress Lifetime Warranty cover?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress Lifetime Warranty covers sagging (more than 1”), loss of shape, splitting or cracking of the foam, and loss of mattress height. The warranty is only valid for customers who have purchased their Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress directly from our website or Layla Sleep authorized marketplaces.<br> <br> Read the full terms and conditions of the <a href="https://help.laylasleep.com/hc/en-us/articles/360008220473-What-are-the-Layla-Mattress-Lifetime-Warranty-Details-" rel="noopener noreferrer" target="_blank">Layla Mattress Lifetime Warranty</a>.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1262"><div class="toggtitle">3. How does the Layla® Mattress 120 Night Trial work?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>It’s simple. Purchase a mattress and sleep on it for up to 120 nights. If for any reason you don’t totally love your Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress, simply return it for a 100% refund - no return fees and no shipping fees are charged for returns. We only ask that you sleep on the mattress for at least 2 weeks before deciding if it’s right for you.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="shipping-delivery-mattress"><h5>Shipping</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1253"><div class="toggtitle">1. How much does the Layla® Mattress weigh?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Here's what each size Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress weighs:</p><p>Twin: 41 lbs</p><p>Twin XL: 44 lbs</p><p>Full: 57 lbs</p><p>Queen: 69 lbs</p><p>King: 87 lbs</p><p>Cal King: 87 lbs</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1250"><div class="toggtitle">2. What size box does the Layla® Mattress come in?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Each Layla<sup>®</sup> mattress is compressed, rolled, and packaged for delivery in boxes with the following dimensions for each size:</p><p>Twin - 42"x15"x15"<br> Twin XL - 42"x15"x15"<br> Full - 45"x19"x19"<br> Queen - 45"x19"x19"<br> King - 45"x19"x19"<br> Cal King - 45"x19"x19"</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1248"><div class="toggtitle">3. How do I track my Layla® Mattress shipment?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>You may track your order at any time with your order number.</p><p>Visit <a href="//laylasleep.com/track-order/">https://laylasleep.com/track-order/</a></p><p>Enter your order number and click the "Track Order" button. If you do not see any tracking information that means that your order has not yet shipped.</p><p>If you created an account when you placed your order, you may check your order status and tracking there as well. Visit <a href="//laylasleep.com/my-account/">https://laylasleep.com/my-account/</a> and sign in or create an account with the email you used to place your order.</p><p>Once your Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress ships, we will send you an email with your tracking number. Allow 3 complete business days after you place your order to receive this email. If you do not receive your tracking email after the third business day you may&nbsp;<a href="https://laylasleep.com/contact-us/">chat with us</a>&nbsp;or email us at <a href="mailto:orders@laylasleep.com">orders@laylasleep.com</a> to check on your order.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_600"><div class="toggtitle">4. How long does it take to get my Layla® Mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Each Layla<sup>®</sup> Mattress is crafted to order and takes 3-5 business days to manufacture and package your mattress. Once shipped, transit times will take from 2-5 business days depending on your location.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_602"><div class="toggtitle">5. Does the Layla® Mattress ship for free?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Shipping to the lower 48 states is FREE! Shipping charges to Alaska, Hawaii, and Canada may apply at checkout.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_604"><div class="toggtitle">6. Where does the Layla® Mattress ship to?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>We ship to the entire USA and Canada.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div _ngcontent-serverapp-c35="" class="col-sm-12"><h3>Layla Hybrid Mattress</h3><div class="row post-faq-row"><div class="col-sm-6" id="about-hybrid-layla-hybrid-mattress"><h5>About Hybrid</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633698"><div class="toggtitle">1. What is a hybrid mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>A hybrid mattress is one that brings together both springs and specialty foams such as memory foam or latex thus combining a more traditional bouncy feel with new-age comfort.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633697"><div class="toggtitle">2. What is the Layla® Hybrid Mattress made from?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Cover:<br> Fabric: 63% Polyester – 26% Rayon – 6% Viscose – 5% Lycra<br> Branded Black Belt: 100% Nylon<br> Branded Handles: 100% Vinyl</p><p>Copper Infused Memory Foam (Soft Side)<br> 2.5” of 3.5 lbs copper infused viscoelastic polyurethane open-cell foam with an IFD (indentation force deflection) of 12 lbs.</p><p>Layla Tri-Zone-Airflow™ Transition Layer (Soft Side)<br> 2” of 1.65 lbs polyurethane open-cell foam with an IFD (indentation force deflection) of 23 lbs. Surface Modification Technology (SMT) shapes are cut .5” deep for added support, airflow, and pressure relief.</p><p>Layla Infinity Edge™ Spring System<br> 6” of individually wrapped 14 gauge pocketed coil springs with dual row 16 gauge springs around the perimeter for edge support.</p><p>Layla Tri-Zone-Airflow™ Transition Layer (Firm Side)<br> 1.5” of 1.65 lbs polyurethane open-cell foam with an IFD (indentation force deflection) of 40 lbs. Surface Modification Technology (SMT) shapes are cut .25” deep for added support, airflow, and pressure relief.</p><p>Copper Infused Memory Foam (Firm Side)<br> 1” of 3.5 lbs copper infused viscoelastic polyurethane open-cell foam with an IFD (indentation force deflection) of 12 lbs.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633686"><div class="toggtitle">3. What’s the difference between the original Layla™ and The Layla Hybrid™?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Both the Layla Mattress and the Layla Hybrid™ are award winning mattresses that would send any sleeper into dream city. The Layla Hybrid™ has all the features and benefits of the original Layla Mattress with the additions of:<br> • An extra 3” in profile<br> • Individually wrapped springs giving a more traditional feel (The original Layla Mattress does not have springs)<br> • Infinity Edge™ support for added edge support<br> • Two handles on each side of the mattress to help flip from the soft side to the firm.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633685"><div class="toggtitle">4. How do I know if this mattress is right for me?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla Hybrid™ is for you if you enjoy the feel of a traditional spring mattress but also would like the new-age comfort of memory foam. Also if you like having the option of being able to try a different firmness by simply flipping your mattress over and you don’t mind the copper particles supporting you and keeping you cool and clean while you sleep.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633684"><div class="toggtitle">5. What are the benefits of this mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>There are many features and benefits to the Layla Hybrid™ mattress provided by each layer:<br> Cover: Our super-soft high quality thick fabric allows for a comfortable sleeping experience and is removable for easy cleaning and maintenance.<br> Copper Infused Memory Foam: Infusing copper into the memory foam provides:<br> - Cooling: Copper pulls heat away from the body creating a cool sleep environment.<br> - Variable Support: When placed under pressure copper particles condense creating a firming response under areas that require additional support such as shoulders and hips<br> - Cleaning: Copper is also anti-microbial and helps kills germs, bacteria, and viruses.<br> Layla Tri-Zone-Airflow™ Foam: The tri-zone layers provide more support in the center of the mattress (for hips and shoulders) and also allow hot air to leave the mattress while cool fresh air flows in.<br> Individually Wrapped Coils<br> With high quality American Made springs individually wrapped in fabric you get individual support for every inch of your body. Springs move independently so when your partner moves around your side of the bed stays put allowing you to sleep soundly through the night.<br> Infinity Edge™ Support<br> Higher gauge springs around the perimeter of the mattress make for better edge support.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633683"><div class="toggtitle">6. Does this mattress contain any harmful VOC’s<i class="fa fa-pl