e they safe?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>All of the foams used in the Layla<sup>®</sup> and Layla Hybrid™ mattress are American Made open cell polyurethane foams that are CertiPUR-US<sup>®</sup> certified. All foams are tested and approved to be completely safe.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633694"><div class="toggtitle">3. Where is the Layla Hybrid™ made?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla Hybrid™ mattress (springs and foam) and cover fabric are made in America.<br> Nylon belt, handles, and zipper are imported from Asia.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_633693"><div class="toggtitle">4. How long after unboxing can I sleep on the mattress?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>We ask that you allow your Layla Hybrid™ to expand for at least two hours after unboxing before use. If the mattress was stored in a cold climate you may need a complete 24 hours for complete decompression.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div _ngcontent-serverapp-c35="" class="col-sm-12"><h3>Layla Kapok Pillow</h3><div class="row post-faq-row"><div class="col-sm-6" id="about-the-pillow-pillow"><h5>About The Pillow</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1226"><div class="toggtitle">1. What is the Layla Pillow?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla Pillow is soft and supportive filled with a mix of Kapok tree fibers and shredded memory foam. The copper infused cover of the pillow is custom crafted to match the Layla Mattress.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1232"><div class="toggtitle">2. What is Kapok?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Kapok is a tree that grows in Indonesia and the seed pod fibers are sustainably harvested for use as fill in the pillow. Kapok fibers are extremely light and airy with more loft than cotton or wool.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1238"><div class="toggtitle">3. Is the memory foam in the Layla Pillow safe?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes. The premium reactive memory foam that is shredded and used as fill in the Layla Pillow is CertiPUR-US<sup>®</sup> certified, meaning the foam is:<br> Made without ozone depleters<br> Made without PBDEs, TDCPP or TCEP (”Tris”) flame retardants<br> Made without mercury, lead, and other heavy metals<br> Made without formaldehyde<br> Made without phthalates regulated by the Consumer Product Safety Commission<br> Low VOC (Volatile Organic Compound) emissions for indoor air quality (less than 0.5 parts per million) so there’s little to no off gassing odor.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1241"><div class="toggtitle">4. How soft is the Layla Pillow?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla Pillow like the Layla Mattress is the perfect balance of soft and supportive. You will feel the plush softness of fluffy Kapok, but still have the support of reactive memory foam to keep your neck happy.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1243"><div class="toggtitle">5. Is the Layla Pillow hypoallergenic?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes. Breathe deep and don’t worry, Kapok is allergy-friendly – and the memory foam used in the Layla Pillow is CertiPUR-US® Certified.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1252"><div class="toggtitle">6. What is the Layla Pillow cover made from?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla Pillow cover is 66% polyester, 30% viscose, 4% poly/lycra, and is woven with copper fibers.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1255"><div class="toggtitle">7. How is copper in Layla Pillow cover beneficial?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Copper fibers woven into the Layla Pillow cover absorb body heat and quickly transfer it away from your noggin. Copper fibers also act as an antimicrobial barrier to keep out the nasty. Although scientifically unverified, many people claim to experience significant health benefits from wearing or using copper infused fabric.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1314"><div class="toggtitle">8. What are the sizes of the Layla Pillow?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla Pillow is available in two sizes:<br> Standard: 18" x 28"<br> King: 18" x 34"</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="care-pillow-pillow"><h5>Care</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_49887"><div class="toggtitle">1. Unboxing the Layla Pillow<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The fill inside your pillow will be compressed and bunched up a bit when you remove it from the box. Don't worry, this is normal. After you remove your pillow from the box, place it on a flat surface and use the palms of your hands or fists to massage the pillow and distribute the fill evenly. This will flatten the pillow out a bit to achieve a pillow height that will support your neck perfectly.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1258"><div class="toggtitle">2. Does the Layla Pillow have an odor?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>You may experience a "new pillow" or “memory foam” smell which can go away in as soon as a few hours but may last a little longer for those who are sensitive to smell. This odor is not harmful to your health but if it bothers you we recommend allowing a couple of hours in a well ventilated room to allow your pillow to air out before placing a pillow case over it.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_1260"><div class="toggtitle">3. Can I wash the Layla Pillow cover?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="tog