i>fitted sheet: 39” x 80” x 14"</li><li>pillowcase: 20” x 30”</li></ul><p><b>Full</b></p><ul><li>flat sheet: 81” x 96”</li><li>fitted sheet: 54” x 75” x 14"</li><li>pillowcase: 20” x 30”</li></ul><p><b>Queen</b></p><ul><li>flat sheet: 90” x 102”</li><li>fitted sheet: 60” x 80” x 14"</li><li>pillowcases: 20” x 30”</li></ul><p><b>King</b></p><ul><li>flat sheet: 108” x 102”</li><li>fitted sheet: 76” x 80” x 14"</li><li>pillowcases: 20” x 40”</li></ul><p><b>Cal King</b></p><ul><li>flat sheet: 108” x 102”</li><li>fitted sheet: 72” x 84” x 14"</li><li>pillowcases: 20” x 40”</li></ul><p><b>Split King</b></p><ul><li>flat sheet: 108” x 102”</li><li>fitted sheet: 39” x 80” x 14”</li><li>pillowcases: 20” x 40”</li></ul></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125481"><div class="toggtitle">6. What are the Layla® Bamboo Sheets made from?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The Layla<sup>®</sup> Bamboo Sheets are made of 100% Viscose from Bamboo. Viscose is described as the process used to turn natural bamboo into fabric. The Bamboo is broken up and dissolved in a solution. Once the bamboo is dissolved, the solution is pressed into fibers and cooled. Finally, these fibers are spun into threads and woven into fabric.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125479"><div class="toggtitle">7. What comes in each Layla® Bamboo Sheet Set?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Each full, queen, king, and cal-king sheet set includes 1 fitted sheet, 1 flat sheet and 2 pillowcases. The twin and twin xl sets includes 1 fitted sheet, 1 flat sheet and 1 pillowcase.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125477"><div class="toggtitle">8. What is the thread count on the Layla® Bamboo Sheet Set?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Bamboo thread count is very different from other fabric thread counts. Our sheets are 300, but the feel is softer than 1,000-thread-count Egyptian cotton.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125475"><div class="toggtitle">9. What are the benefits of having sheets made from Bamboo fibers?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Bamboo is softer, more durable, cooler, and more breathable than traditional cotton or polyester sheets. The Layla Bamboo set is also hypoallergenic, antibacterial, and moisture wicking so you can enjoy a dry, clean, and cool sleep.</p><p>Using bamboo also has environmental benefits since bamboo is grown without pesticides or chemical fertilizers, requires no irrigation, rarely needs replanting, grows rapidly and can be harvested in 3-5 years, and produces 35% more oxygen than equivalent trees.</p><p>Additionally, bamboo is a critical element in the balance of oxygen and carbon dioxide in the atmosphere and is an excellent soil erosion inhibitor.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125473"><div class="toggtitle">10. Is the Layla® Bamboo Sheet Set right for me?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>If you’re someone who loses sleep from sweating or sleeping hot, or you’re just in need of very comfortable sheets, then the Layla<sup>®</sup> Bamboo Sheets are right for you. Bamboo fabric is breathable, thermal regulating, wicks moisture better than polyester performance fabrics, will resist odor and is absorbent, keeping you dryer and more comfortable than any cotton or polyester fabrics.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125471"><div class="toggtitle">11. Is the Layla® Bamboo Sheet Set Hypo-allergenic?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes! Bamboo is naturally hypo-allergenic and anti-bacterial. Bamboo sheets prevent allergies because they reduce the amount of moisture in your bed that attract allergens and dust mites.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125469"><div class="toggtitle">12. Is the Layla® Bamboo Bed Sheet Eco-friendly?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Absolutely. The Bamboo used in the Layla<sup>®</sup> Bamboo Sheets are naturally made without any pesticides or fertilizers. The Bamboo plant requires very little water and regenerates extremely fast, making it a great purchase for any green thumb.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125467"><div class="toggtitle">13. How deep are the Layla® Bed Sheets?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>All our fitted sheets have a 15-inch deep pocket, ensuring a generous fit over even the deepest mattresses.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="care-layla-bamboo-sheets-layla-bamboo-sheets"><h5>Care</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125465"><div class="toggtitle">1. How do I wash my Layla® Bamboo Sheets?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Machine wash cold water.<br>Do not bleach.<br>Do not use fabric softer.<br>Tumble dry low heat - Remove promptly.<br>Iron on low (optional).</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125463"><div class="toggtitle">2. How long will my Layla® Bamboo Sheets last?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>All Layla<sup>®</sup> Sheets are constructed with the highest of quality materials and engineered to last many years if properly cared for. In fact, the Layla<sup>®</sup> Bamboo Bed Sheets get better after every wash and never feel coarse. The Layla<sup>®</sup> Bamboo Sheets have been tested to maintain their original quality up to 1,000 washes.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="trial-period-warranty-returns-layla-bamboo-sheets-layla-bamboo-sheets"><h5>Trial Period/Warranty Returns</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_125461"><div class="toggtitle">1. What is the warranty on the Layla® Bamboo Sheets?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>We provide a 5-year w