odification Technology (SMT) relief pressure and promote airflow. Nothing but the best for you and your furry companion.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_613817"><div class="toggtitle">5. Is the Layla Pet Bed™ liquid proof?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The fabric surrounding The Layla Pet Bed™ is liquid resistant while the cushion is liquid proof forcing liquid to bead up which makes for easy cleaning.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_613816"><div class="toggtitle">6. Is the Layla Pet Bed™ safe for my pet?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Absolutely! All the foams used in the pet bed are CertiPUR-US<sup>®</sup> certified safe and the fabrics are made for common home use.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="shipping-layla-pet-bed-layla-pet-bed"><h5>Shipping</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_703164"><div class="toggtitle">1. How do I track my Layla Pet Bed shipment?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>You may track your order at any time with your order number.</p><p>Visit <a href="//laylasleep.com/track-order/">https://laylasleep.com/track-order/</a></p><p>Enter your order number and click the "Track Order" button. If you do not see any tracking information that means that your order has not yet shipped.</p><p>If you created an account when you placed your order, you may check your order status and tracking there as well. Visit <a href="//laylasleep.com/my-account/">https://laylasleep.com/my-account/</a> and sign in or create an account with the email you used to place your order.</p><p>Once your Layla Pet Bed ships, we will send you an email with your tracking number. Allow 3 complete business days after you place your order to receive this email. If you do not receive your tracking email after the third business day you may chat with us or email us at <a href="mailto:orders@laylasleep.com">orders@laylasleep.com</a> to check on your order.</p></div></div></div></div></div><div _ngcontent-serverapp-c35="" class="col-sm-12"><h3>Layla General FAQ'S</h3><div class="row post-faq-row"><div class="col-sm-6" id="layla-mattress-layla-general-faqs"><h5>Layla Mattress</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433731"><div class="toggtitle">1. What is copper gel infused memory foam?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Copper Gel Memory Foam is made from a material called viscoelastic. It is used in the mattress to offer cooler sleep and also assist with pressure relief. Gel foam maintains a cool and comfortable sleep environment all night.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433729"><div class="toggtitle">2. Is a Copper infused bed good for sleeping?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>If you use a copper infused mattress, you will get a cool and comfortable night's sleep. As copper is anti-bacterial and anti-microbial, it is good for your health. Copper helps maintain immune function, blood vessels, bones, nerves, etc.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433727"><div class="toggtitle">3. How can a copper infused mattress benefit us?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>A copper mattress is super supportive for your body as copper is the second-most conductive element in the world. It is beneficial for our bodies as it helps to keep heat and germs away from your mattress.<br> By maintaining iron levels within your blood, copper can improve blood flow. As an essential nutrient, it offers health benefits that allow you to recover faster after a workout or sporting activity.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433725"><div class="toggtitle">4. What is the best mattress for hot sleepers?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>If you are a hot sleeper and want to stay cool at night, memory foam is one of the best materials which is cool enough for your needs. Choose a Copper Infused Memory Foam mattress since memory foam is partially plant-based and it is an effective way of keeping cool.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="layla-pillow-layla-general-faqs"><h5>Layla Kapok Pillow</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433737"><div class="toggtitle">1. What is the best type of pillow?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>It depends on your sleep style that what type of pillow is best for you. You can choose the right pillow according to your sleeping position. If you are a side sleeper, you need a firmer pillow with a thicker side. If you are a stomach sleeper, you may need a soft pillow. And if you are a Back sleeper, you may need a flat pillow. It will keep your head and neck aligned.<br> It is better to choose a pillow that works for you in all your sleeping positions.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433735"><div class="toggtitle">2. Is it better for your neck to sleep without a pillow?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>If you feel comfortable sleeping without pillow then it is okay. But some people who feel uncomfortable without a pillow can use a soft pillow. You should avoid using too high or hard of a pillow as it can cause neck or shoulder pain.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433733"><div class="toggtitle">3. Is Kapok environmentally friendly?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Kapok is one of the most popular eco filling and an attractive alternative to other fill types like down, feather or synthetic foam. It is soft &amp; silky natural non-toxic fiber.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="layla-foundation-layla-general-faqs"><h5>Layla Foundation</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433739"><div class="toggtitle">1. Do I need a mattress foundation?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>If you want to raise the height of a mattress to make it easier to get in and out of bed then definitely it's needed. Mattress foundations are typically placed on top of a wooden or metal bed frame that is connected to the headboard and footboard.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="layla-bed-frame-layla-general-faqs"><h5>Layla Bed Frame</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433741"><div class="toggtitle">1. What are the types of bed frames?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>These are four types of bed frames:<br> 1-Standard metal bed frame<br> 2-Wood platform bed frame<br> 3-Metal platform bed frame<br> 4-Adjustable platform bed frame</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="layla-topper-layla-general-faqs-layla-general-faqs"><h5>Layla Topper</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433747"><div class="toggtitle">1. Is a mattress topper a good idea?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes, mattress toppers have been effective in enhancing the comfort or softness level of new and old mattresses. Choosing mattress topper is always a good idea.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433745"><div class="toggtitle">2. How do I choose a memory foam topper?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>There are many points you need to have in your mind before choosing a memory foam topper. Most importantly, check the density of your memory foam, select the thickness, and choose a topper size that will fit your bed.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433743"><div class="toggtitle">3. Do memory foam mattress toppers really work?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes, the memory foam mattress topper really works. It helps make sleeping more comfortable and reduces pressure points. If we talk about thickness, most memory foam toppers are either 1,2,3 or 4 inches thick. 1 to 2 inches usually provides a little extra comfort but it can be quite firm. It is good for those who just need a little extra comfort and support for the body.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="layla-bamboo-sheet-layla-general-faqs"><h5>Layla Bamboo Sheet</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433751"><div class="toggtitle">1. Are bamboo sheets better than cotton sheets?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Yes, bamboo sheets are better than cotton sheets. It has a higher thread count which makes it softer and durable. Moreover, it is considered naturally more breathable than cotton. It has the ability to absorb sweat and does not follow to the human body, even in the hottest temperatures.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433749"><div class="toggtitle">2. What is the best quality bamboo sheets?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>People consider bamboo sheets since they are naturally more breathable than cotton. It helps to absorb sweat and does not follow the human body, even in the hottest temperatures.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6" id="layla-weighted-blanket-layla-general-faqs-layla-general-faqs"><h5>Layla Weighted Blanket</h5><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433759"><div class="toggtitle">1. How do I choose a weighted blanket?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>The main step in buying a weighted blanket is determining the right weight for you. So your first step should be to pick the one that's 10 percent of your body weight. Such a blanket choice is a good fit and will provide you real comfort during times of stress.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433757"><div class="toggtitle">2. What is the science behind weighted blankets?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Weighted blankets are used to help ease anxiety, increase oxytocin in the brain and help individuals with sensory processing disorders to feel more relaxed.<br> A weighted blanket is filled with hypoallergenic, non-toxic polypropylene pellets. These pellets give weight to the blanket, which should generally be around 10 percent of the user’s body weight.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433755"><div class="toggtitle">3. Do weighted blankets help with anxiety?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>According to some studies, we feel less anxious due to the weight of Weighted blankets because it delivers a type of therapy called deep pressure touch stimulation. Moreover, a few small studies have looked at the effect of weighted blankets on anxiety and insomnia in adults.</p></div></div><div class="sep-faq" id="accor_433753"><div class="toggtitle">4. What is a weighted blanket?<i class="fa fa-plus" aria-hidden="true"></i></div><div class="toggcontent"><p>Weighted blankets are the heavy blankets (typically 15 pounds or more) filled with a material such as plastic pellets. You feel deep pressure under all of that weight. However, some weighted blankets can be hotter so that you can enjoy the benefits of a weighted blanket, especially in cold.</p></div></div></div></div></div></div></div>
